description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 4 Generic Assistant Practitioner - Acute In-Patient Team &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Nottingham University Hospitals has an opportunity to for an enthusiastic and motivated individual to join our Acute Physiotherapy and OT In-Patient Team at Queens Medical Centre, working as a Band 4 Generic Assistant Practitioner.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is an opportunity for an individual with experience of working within acute medicine and therapy services to increase their knowledge and develop new skills. This post will support the expansion for acute medical beds on the QMC campus. It is a permanent position, working full time with adults at QMC. We are looking for an individual who is keen and a conscientious team player with the ability to use their initiative, work flexibly and be self –motivated, who can demonstrate excellent communication skills and has a real enthusiasm.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As a Band 4 Generic Practitioner you will work closely with the friendly and dynamic physiotherapy team, supporting patients. You will have your own caseload of patients and will be expected to assess, treat and discharge patients. You will also work closely with the physiotherapy and OT team with those patients who need more than one therapist to treat.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;There will be opportunities to build leadership and management skills supervising assistants and band 3 staff. At NUH we are committed to providing an extensive framework of Induction, training and support to help you develop your full potential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You must have a NVQ Level 3 or equivalent, GCSE or equivalent in Maths and English and good IT skills.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt; Previous experience at band 3 level within acute medicine will be desirable. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be required to work on a rota system to cover weekends and bank holidays.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
